article.description: Rebecca Greenwell had 17 points and 11 rebounds and No. 19 Duke reached 20 wins for an Atlantic Coast Conference record 21st straight season on Sunday with a 60-35 win over Clemson.
article.headline: Greenwell carries No. 19 Duke women past Clemson 60-35.
article.linkText: Greenwell carries No. 19 Duke women past Clemson 60-35.
article.story:
CLEMSON, S.C. --  Rebecca Greenwell had 17 points and 11 rebounds and No. 19 Duke reached 20 wins for an Atlantic Coast Conference record 21st straight season on Sunday with a 60-35 win over Clemson.

Erin Mathias added 12 points and nine rebounds and Leaonna Odom had 10 points for the Blue Devils (20-6, 9-4). Lexie Brown was held to a season-low six points on 2-of-12 shooting but hit a 3-pointer for the 25th straight game, an ACC best that matches the school record. Brown had nine assists.

Aliyah Collier led the Tigers (11-15, 1-12), who have lost seven straight, with 11 points.

Duke limited Clemson to 27 percent shooting in the first half and opened a 30-14 lead. The Blue Devils snared 28 rebounds, a season-high for a half, and went on to a 45-28 advantage on the boards.
